    'body' => '
>GDW is closing down.  One of the oldest companies in the
>industry, founded in 1973...stops selling product January 19th
>and expects to be shut down by the end of February.

1.  It\'s a shame about GDW closing down, but companies come and
companies go.  GDW hasn\'t been the focus of my attentions, it\'s
been the games..particularly Traveller.  I\'m sorry to see TW2k go
down the tubes too!

2.  I haven\'t been enthused about where GDW has been carrying
Traveller the last few years..never liked the Virus, even the
rebellion wasn\'t really where I wanted to to play or run games.

3.  SJG *might* be a good new owner for the Traveller products.
Are they interested in buying *all* of Traveller?  What about 2300AD?
What about TW2K?  Personally, I see them as a package.  But
anyway, SJ Games is an active and innovative publisher.  I like
GURPS well enough for it to be my second favorite system.  <g>
But frankly, I suspect they would treat Traveller more as source
books or world books than a system, and GURPify it as much as
possible.  I *could* live with that, but it wouldn\'t be my first
choice.

4.  Marc Miller has written that Traveller rights devolve to him.
I don\'t know why Mr Miller walked away from GDW and Traveller a
few years ago.  I\'ve heard it was because he was \'burned out\' on
trying to make a living selling games, but that\'s only second
hand rumor.  Would Marc be able or willing to do what it takes to
keep Traveller in print?  What versions of Traveller will he
support?  Will he have control over how Traveller history
develops?  What does he make of the Virus, for example?  <g> Will
he control TW2K and 2300AD, or just Traveller..and does that
include TNE?

5.  Wherever Traveller ends up, I think it will survive.  IMHO, it is
the only really good SF based gaming system around and as such
we\'ll be using it whether it\'s in print or not.  Until something
better comes along, and nothing has come along now has it?

6.  Whoever picks up Traveller will be in a position to do
something I\'d really like to see..a divorce between the Traveller
game *system* and the Traveller game *history*.  Yes, yes I
know..so don\'t start flaming me!  <g> I realize that the detailed
history is what sets Traveller apart from everything else, so I\'m
not suggesting that we dump it.  Just that we sanction and
develop more than one!

What I\'d like to see is a general game system (that\'s what the
TNE rules were going to be, I think), and several Official
Histories.  Three that I can think of right now:  a. the Virus
collapsed history; b. the Rebellion induced Hard Times history; c.
the Classic Imperium where the Rebellion failed and no Virus was
ever released.  Maybe there could be other Histories that are
officially sanctioned and supported as well, but that are still
based on the Same System Of Rules.

Well that\'s my two cents anyway.

Eris Reddoch


