    'body' => '
..and what was I doing when GDW blew up?  Solid, productive work like
building Massive Imperial Warships!

I had difficulty trying to translate the data given in Battle Rider\'s
ships into Brilliant Lancer\'s terms.  The ship\'s in BR were designed to
mesh and balance each other, and only roughly fit into BL restrictions.
Major problems were hit with...
      ... the massive armour levels of some ship\'s.  Problems centred
      around the mass of the armour, the size of the power drive and the
      volume of G-fuel needed - while still trying to fit in those
      serious meson gun\'s into the hull. (Why, why didn\'t the Imperial Navy
      use particle accellerators instead?  Mass, energy and especially crew
      requirements would have made my job rather easier)
      ... the meson screens.  The size of those meson screen machinery
      get\'s really, REALLY out of control, devouring space like Microsoft
      Software!

I don\'t believe that in ANY instance I was able to exactly match the
stat\'s given in BR!  If anyone here has a lot of time on their hand,
(over the holidays, it took me about a day to translate one ship, with
eight capital ships in total - by pencil and calculator, of course!) they
may wish to try and get closer to the BR stat\'s fot the ship\'s.

I\'m just glad that the bloody things fly.

In all instances, I totally ignored the rules regarding surface area
needed for the jump drive.  Had I followed those rules, the (already
weakened) meson screens would have to be scrapped: in many instances,
even EM Masking would have to be dropped.

*****----*****----*****

The Tigress is the largest of the TL F, line-of-battle ship\'s in the
Imperial Navy.  Unlike many of the IN\'s capital ships are focused on a
single mission, the 500,000 disp. Tigress is a multimission dreadnaught,
combining the functions of a fighter carrier with a big-time meson gun.
Standard Imperial Practice is to keep one squadron of Tigress\' in each
sector.  Further information can be found in the Classic book \'Fighting
Ship\'s\', which gives out Classic Trav stat\'s for it.

NOTE: The Classic Tigress is built to support 50-ton fighters: however, I
chose to use lighter 15-ton fighters simply because I didn\'t catch this
fact until AFTER I had built the Tigress, and had no intention to do the
numerous fixes (and design a 50-ton fighter!) that a better translation
would require.

NOTE: No, this ship isn\'t included in Battle Rider.

