    'body' => '
The Triumph/Gallant is the standard TL F tender group, in mass production
throughout Strephon\'s reign (he was coronated around 1075).  Gallant\'s
are a bit on the small side for a ship-of-the-line: it is, however, a lot
cheaper than a jumpship with equivelant firepower, armour and mobility.

Since the Fourth Frontier War, most tender groups have been kept as a
strategic reserve.  This is due to the vulnerability of tender groups to
the loss/emergency flight of the tender: without the tender, the rider\'s
have no way to retreat from the system, and may be destroyed at leisure by
the opposing navy.

The Triumph has 465 troops as part of its standard complement: if the
tender is expected to be able to overall it\'s riders, or operate for over
8 months without using a naval base for maintainance, the troops can be
replaced with maintenance personnel.  About 154 men are needed to provide
maintenance and overhauls for 1 battle rider.

A critical weakness in battle tenders revolves around surface area.
Most tenders use grapples or docking rings to hold their riders: however,
these items devour so much surface area that they render EM Masking unviable.
The Triumph/Gallant tender group shines in this area, as the Triumph uses
a 10% flicker black globe as both additional shielding and a \'cloaking
device\', allowing the Gallants to deployed in more daring and effective
formations.  The black globe was introduced rather late in the Triumph\'s
development, so it has it\'s own HPG to store energy, rather than using
the ship\'s jump drives.

The projected StarLord/Navarch TL F tender group, currently under
development in Core and Massilia, is expected to be the first to fully
utilize the potential of black globes in combat.  With the tender using
it\'s immense jump drives to store energy, this tender group is expected
to revolutionize naval assaults on heavily defended systems,
substantually reducing ship losses due to massive underground meson sites.

